WEBVTT

00:00:55.953 --> 00:01:00.707
than opioid overdoses
and car accidents combined.

00:01:01.488 --> 00:01:04.868
But you can't take medicine
if you can't afford it.

00:01:05.280 --> 00:01:10.388
Today, the average household
spends 3,000 dollars a year

00:01:10.412 --> 00:01:11.983
on medications.

00:01:12.007 --> 00:01:14.929
About a third of folks who are uninsured

00:01:14.953 --> 00:01:18.720
said that they stopped
taking medicine as prescribed

00:01:18.744 --> 00:01:20.169
because of cost.

00:01:20.193 --> 00:01:22.574
Even folks with insurance,

00:01:22.598 --> 00:01:25.871
if they make under 35,000 dollars a year,

00:01:25.895 --> 00:01:29.493
half of them report
skipping the medications

00:01:29.517 --> 00:01:31.355
if their insurance doesn't cover it.